        "# Exercise 1.4.1\n",
        "\n",
        "## Task 1\n",
        "\n",
        "Suppose you take out a loan with a principal amount of #100,000. If the annual interest rate on the loan is 5% and you plan to repay it in 3 years, how much interest will you owe at the end of the loan term?\n",
        "\n",
        "For this task write a function called `interest()` that accepts the 3 parameters as input arguments and calculates the amount of interest owed at the end of the loan term.\n",
        "The 3 input arguments should be in the given order:\n",
        "- The principle loan amount\n",
        "- The annual interest rate\n",
        "- The number of years in which the loan should be repayed\n",
        "\n",
        "Once you have written the function, call it with the provided parameters:\n",
        "- Principal (P) = #100,000\n",
        "- Rate (R) = 5% per annum\n",
        "- Time (T) = 3 years"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gxRkTASVWq07"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Solution\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Vt-hGL60Wfzn",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "95a49736-dd0b-4f8a-98fe-52c752998143"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Principal (P): #100,000.00\n",
            "Rate (R): 5.0%\n",
            "Time (T): 3 years\n",
            "------------------------------\n",
            "Interest owed (I): #15,000.00\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "### Run your function with the provided parameters here:\n",
        "\n",
        "def interest(principal_amount, annual_rate, time_years):\n",
        "  \"\"\"\n",
        "  Calculates the simple interest owed at the end of a loan term.\n",
        "\n",
        "  Args:\n",
        "    principal_amount (float or int): The initial principal loan amount (P).\n",
        "    annual_rate (float): The annual interest rate (R) as a decimal (e.g., 0.05 for 5%).\n",
        "    time_years (float or int): The number of years (T) in which the loan is repaid.\n",
        "\n",
        "  Returns:\n",
        "    float: The total amount of simple interest owed (I).\n",
        "  \"\"\"\n",
        "  # Simple Interest Formula: I = P * R * T\n",
        "  interest_owed = principal_amount * annual_rate * time_years\n",
        "  return interest_owed\n",
        "\n",
        "# Provided parameters:\n",
        "P = 100000  # Principal (#100,000)\n",
        "R = 0.05    # Rate (5% per annum)\n",
        "T = 3       # Time (3 years)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Call the function with the provided parameters:\n",
        "interest_result = interest(P, R, T)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Principal (P): #{P:,.2f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Rate (R): {R * 100}%\")\n",
        "print(f\"Time (T): {T} years\")\n",
        "print(\"-\" * 30)\n",
        "print(f\"Interest owed (I): #{interest_result:,.2f}\")\n"
      ]
    },
