      "source": [
        "## Task 2\n",
        "\n",
        "Write a function called `celsius_to_fahrenheit()` that converts a temperature from degrees Celsius to degrees Fahrenheit.\n",
        "\n",
        "You can use this formula:\n",
        "\n",
        "$T_c ∗ 1.8 + 32$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $T_c$ is the temperature in degrees celsius to be converted.\n",
        "\n",
        "Once you have written the function, use it to convert the following temperatures from Celsius to Fahrenheit:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. 100\n",
        "\n",
        "2. 75\n",
        "\n",
        "3. 120"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T4OzDfZ6Wq09"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Solution"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "A5ReJKRgWq09",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "6e985af0-2156-4235-f38f-2b22afad0c8b"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "--- Temperature Conversions ---\n",
            "100°C is equal to 212.00°F\n",
            "75°C is equal to 167.00°F\n",
            "120°C is equal to 248.00°F\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "### CG T2\n",
        "### Write your function here:\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# 1. Define the function celsius_to_fahrenheit()\n",
        "# ----------------------------------------------------\n",
        "def celsius_to_fahrenheit(celsius_temp):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Converts a temperature from degrees Celsius to degrees Fahrenheit.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Parameters:\n",
        "    celsius_temp (float): The temperature in degrees Celsius (Tc).\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns:\n",
        "    float: The converted temperature in degrees Fahrenheit (Tf).\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    # Conversion Formula: Tf = Tc * 1.8 + 32\n",
        "    fahrenheit_temp = celsius_temp * 1.8 + 32\n",
        "    return fahrenheit_temp\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------------------------------\n",
        "# 2. Convert the specified temperatures\n",
        "# ----------------------------------------------------\n",
        "temperatures_celsius = [100, 75, 120]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"--- Temperature Conversions ---\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Loop through the list and print the conversion for each value\n",
        "for temp_c in temperatures_celsius:\n",
        "    # Call the function\n",
        "    temp_f = celsius_to_fahrenheit(temp_c)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Print the result\n",
        "    print(f\"{temp_c}°C is equal to {temp_f:.2f}°F\")\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
